headline: ACS, BlackRock launch 2 billion euro data centre joint venture
summary: MADRID (Reuters) -Spain's ACS and BlackRock's Global Infrastructure Partners have created a joint venture to develop ​an initial 2 billion euro ($2.33 billion),‌ 1.7 gigawatt portfolio of data centres, the Spanish company said on Friday.  Both ‌companies will have a 50% stake in the joint venture, ACS said.  ACS said it is also reviewing a pipeline of potential projects exceeding 11 GW across North America, Europe, and ​Asia-Pacific that will be part of the joint venture.
